search tips:

  • Please pay attention that all words are written correctly.
  • Define your search request exactly (e.g. "iPhone 4" 16GB black instead of iPhone).
  • Phrases in quotation marks ("product") are searched exactly in that order.
  • Words with a hyphen in front are excluded from searching (e.g., Nexus 7 -16GB 3G).
  • For new products, a switch from "used" to "new" makes sense. (e.g., "HTC One" -S -SV -X -XL -V -VX)

data.name: apikey
data.description: This is your api key.

data.name: category
data.description: This is the category of your requested product that gets evaluated.

data.name: enddate
data.description: Sets the end date of the analysis period.

data.name: keyword
data.description: This is the name of your product/article.

data.name: language
data.description: This identifier sets the language of the API output.

data.name: listing
data.description: Determines whether the calculation should be done with auction or buyitnow products.

data.name: startdate
data.description: Sets the start date of the analysis period. Please note that you can only go 183 days back in time.

data.name: state
data.description: The state attribute determines whether the calculation should be done with used or new products.
The actual search routine. Provides you with statistical data based on your given product and category.

data.name: Object category

description: Bidvoy is a product value tracking service for eBay. By examining eBay auction data, Bidvoy tracks price trends for products over time, allowing you to examine that products average price, changes in value over time, and price margin. Use Bidvoy's information to decide when to buy, or sell, a product. Bidvoy offer a simple API for developers.
